00:00:26,510 --> 00:00:28,060
one dimensional motion as an example.

9
00:00:28,060 --> 00:00:31,340
And let me begin with a false law of physics.

10
00:00:32,140 --> 00:00:35,200
I think I called it last time Aristotle's Law.

11
00:00:37,520 --> 00:00:40,280
Aristotle thought that in order to keep an object moving,

12
00:00:40,480 --> 00:00:43,240
you had to continuously exert a force on it.

13
00:00:44,280 --> 00:00:44,980
Of course,

14
00:00:44,980 --> 00:00:45,840
we know that's not true.

15
00:00:45,980 --> 00:00:48,660
An object moving through free space

16
00:00:48,660 --> 00:00:51,340
under its own inertia will keep moving

17
00:00:51,340 --> 00:00:52,700
without an external force,

18
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:57,820
but Aristotle's Law is a consistent mathematical law.

19
00:00:58,060 --> 00:00:58,760
So let me write it down.

20
00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:00,160
What it says,

21
00:01:00,160 --> 00:01:02,760
I don't know that Aristotle,

22
00:01:02,760 --> 00:01:03,320
of course,

23
00:01:03,320 --> 00:01:04,180
ever said it this way.

24
00:01:04,239 --> 00:01:05,099
I'll say it this way.

25
00:01:06,640 --> 00:01:07,900
I would call it my own

26
00:01:07,900 --> 00:01:09,160
law except I know that it's wrong,

27
00:01:09,360 --> 00:01:10,840
so there's not much percentage in it.

28
00:01:14,259 --> 00:01:15,460
Force is equal,

29
00:01:15,460 --> 00:01:17,860
let's put a constant in and call it mass,

30
00:01:17,860 --> 00:01:19,420
times velocity.

31
00:01:19,860 --> 00:01:21,450
And we can make this a vector

32
00:01:21,450 --> 00:01:23,040
equation or we can simply make it

33
00:01:23,040 --> 00:01:25,060
a one dimensional equation along an axis.

34
00:01:25,720 --> 00:01:28,040
It says that without force we have our force.

35
00:01:28,060 --> 00:01:29,280
you can't have any velocity.

36
00:01:29,280 --> 00:01:31,220
If you remove the force,

37
00:01:31,220 --> 00:01:33,900
an object will instantly come to rest.

38
00:01:34,580 --> 00:01:35,640
Wrong equation.

39
00:01:35,640 --> 00:01:39,320
But we can also write this,

40
00:01:39,320 --> 00:01:39,760
of course,

41
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:44,420
F equals mass times dx dt.

42
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:47,160
And just to remind you,

43
00:01:47,160 --> 00:01:51,580
I often use the notation dot on top of

44
00:01:51,580 --> 00:01:56,000
a symbol to indicate derivative with respect to time.

45
00:01:57,140 --> 00:01:58,680
So that's Aristotle's law.

46
00:01:58,680 --> 00:01:59,840
Now,

47
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:01,360
what do you need...oh,

48
00:02:01,360 --> 00:02:02,980
and we'll also assume something else.

49
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:07,080
We'll assume that the force law is a law which tells you

50
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:10,840
what the force on the object is if you know where it is.

51
00:02:11,460 --> 00:02:13,020
Where the object is.

52
00:02:13,020 --> 00:02:15,960
So let's write F of x.

53
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:23,240
F of x is equal to mass...well,

54
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:24,020
that's fine.

55
00:02:24,020 --> 00:02:25,560
Mass times dx dt.

56
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:27,900
Now,

57
00:02:27,900 --> 00:02:31,000
I say that in order to follow the system,

58
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:34,520
all you need to know is,

59
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:36,640
at the initial starting point,

60
00:02:36,640 --> 00:02:38,340
all you need to know is the position.

61
00:02:38,580 --> 00:02:40,420
You don't need to know the velocity.

62
00:02:40,420 --> 00:02:42,260
How do I know that?

63
00:02:42,260 --> 00:02:43,060
Well,

64
00:02:43,060 --> 00:02:43,760
look at this equation.

65
00:02:44,060 --> 00:02:47,940
Supposing you knew that time t equals zero,

66
00:02:47,940 --> 00:02:48,980
this is x,

67
00:02:48,980 --> 00:02:52,340
the vertical axis doesn't mean anything right now.

68
00:02:52,900 --> 00:02:55,100
Supposing we knew the particle was at x.

69
00:02:56,700 --> 00:02:57,260
Then,

70
00:02:57,260 --> 00:03:00,720
we would instantly know the force on it.

71
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:01,700
Why?

72
00:03:01,700 --> 00:03:04,440
Because the force is a known function of position.

73
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:06,060
But from that,

74
00:03:06,060 --> 00:03:08,020
