182
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:11,980
And that says,

183
00:07:11,980 --> 00:07:12,860
first of all,

184
00:07:12,860 --> 00:07:13,960
we have df by dt.

185
00:07:13,980 --> 00:07:14,280
And that's the derivative of f by dx.

186
00:07:15,980 --> 00:07:17,620
Times dv by dt.

187
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:19,640
But that's just the acceleration.

188
00:07:20,580 --> 00:07:21,720
That's one term.

189
00:07:22,340 --> 00:07:24,880
That's the term coming from differentiating velocity.

190
00:07:24,940 --> 00:07:27,300
And then the other term is

191
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:29,660
gotten by differentiating df by dx.

192
00:07:30,819 --> 00:07:33,000
We're differentiating with respect to time.

193
00:07:33,740 --> 00:07:36,910
But that's just the second derivative of f

194
00:07:36,910 --> 00:07:40,080
with respect to x squared times the velocity.

195
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:41,940
Forget this for a moment.

196
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:47,130
The time derivative of f of the derivative of f is the

197
00:07:47,130 --> 00:07:51,620
second derivative of f with respect to x times the velocity again.

198
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:54,120
It's exactly the same thing as over here,

199
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:56,820
except applied to the derivative of f.

200
00:07:57,960 --> 00:07:58,520
Now,

201
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:01,020
we have to multiply that by another velocity.

202
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:03,160
Okay.

203
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:05,750
Derivative of f with respect to

204
00:08:05,750 --> 00:08:07,980
x times the velocity times another velocity.

205
00:08:08,280 --> 00:08:09,540
The upshot is,

206
00:08:09,540 --> 00:08:10,440
in fact,

207
00:08:10,440 --> 00:08:11,300
we do know the jerk.

208
00:08:11,940 --> 00:08:12,240
We,

209
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:13,580
a moment ago,

210
00:08:13,580 --> 00:08:17,120
convinced ourselves that if we know the initial position,

211
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:20,540
we also know both the velocity and the acceleration.

212
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:22,320
Well,

213
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:25,460
all that goes in here is velocity

214
00:08:25,460 --> 00:08:28,600
and acceleration and knowledge of the force law.

215
00:08:29,620 --> 00:08:30,180
So,

216
00:08:30,180 --> 00:08:31,800
you also know the jerk.

217
00:08:32,159 --> 00:08:34,149
I don't know what the term

218
00:08:34,149 --> 00:08:36,140
for the derivative of the jerk is.

219
00:08:36,580 --> 00:08:37,580
The putz,

220
00:08:37,580 --> 00:08:38,000
the schmuck,

221
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:38,380
I don't know.

222
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:38,640
But,

223
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:39,000
uh...

224
00:08:40,659 --> 00:08:41,919
I don't know what the term is.

225
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:42,340
I don't know what it's called.

226
00:08:43,520 --> 00:08:47,180
But you can see the pattern differentiated again,

227
00:08:47,180 --> 00:08:51,860
and each time you can deduce the next derivative.

228
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:52,860
That,

229
00:08:52,860 --> 00:08:53,320
in effect,

230
00:08:53,320 --> 00:08:56,400
says you can build up the entire motion if all

231
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:59,480
