00:12:55,740 --> 00:12:56,620
I gave you the example,

342
00:12:56,620 --> 00:12:58,000
a couple of examples,

343
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,840
where energy conservation fails.

344
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:01,600
For example,

345
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:03,060
if there's friction forces,

346
00:13:03,060 --> 00:13:03,680
of course,

347
00:13:03,680 --> 00:13:05,780
energy conservation really does work.

348
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:09,630
It works if you were to follow the heat

349
00:13:09,630 --> 00:13:12,300
and everything else that's produced by the sliding eraser.

350
00:13:12,980 --> 00:13:15,340
But if you ignore all that and just

351
00:13:15,340 --> 00:13:17,700
think of friction forces slowing the eraser down,

352
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:19,980
it would seem that the energy,

353
00:13:19,980 --> 00:13:21,200
the kinetic energy,

354
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,520
the energy of motion,

355
00:13:23,660 --> 00:13:24,940
suddenly goes away,

356
00:13:24,940 --> 00:13:29,480
and it's not compensated for any change in potential energy.

357
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:30,760
So,

358
00:13:30,760 --> 00:13:31,580
there are options.

359
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:33,320
There are obviously formulas that you can

360
00:13:33,320 --> 00:13:35,040
write down which would not conserve energy.

361
00:13:36,300 --> 00:13:37,820
I'll give you another example.

362
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:39,620
The other example was the spiral staircase.

363
00:13:40,240 --> 00:13:41,760
The spiral staircase,

364
00:13:41,760 --> 00:13:43,160
you can think of it this way.

365
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:45,360
Supposing you have a force law

366
00:13:47,140 --> 00:13:49,320
that always pushes you around

367
00:13:49,320 --> 00:13:51,500
a circle in the same direction.

368
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:54,640
The force always points around the circle.

369
00:13:55,040 --> 00:13:57,270
Let's not worry for the moment where

370
00:13:57,270 --> 00:13:59,500
the centrifugal force takes you off the circle.

371
00:13:59,660 --> 00:14:00,620
Let's pretend that the force is

372
00:14:00,620 --> 00:14:01,580
always pushing you around the circle.

373
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:02,900
Let's pretend that there's a good solid barrier,

374
00:14:02,900 --> 00:14:04,280
another force,

375
00:14:04,420 --> 00:14:06,820
which keeps the particle from moving off the circle.

376
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:09,380
And what's going to happen?

377
00:14:09,580 --> 00:14:11,200
If the force is always pushing you

378
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:12,820
around the circle in the same direction,

379
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:14,530
the particle is going to

380
00:14:14,530 --> 00:14:15,980
get faster and faster and faster.

381
00:14:16,700 --> 00:14:17,580
And it's clear,

382
00:14:17,580 --> 00:14:20,660
by the time it comes back to the same position,

383
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:22,800
it will be going faster.

384
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:27,290
There's no possibility of a

385
00:14:27,290 --> 00:14:31,080
conservation of potential in kinetic energy

386
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:34,080
because you've come back to exactly the same spot.

387
00:14:34,860 --> 00:14:36,580
So therefore the potential energy,

388
00:14:36,580 --> 00:14:37,380
if there is any,

389
00:14:37,380 --> 00:14:38,240
will be the same.

390
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:40,460
But the kinetic energy has increased.

391
00:14:40,780 --> 00:14:42,020
And it'll keep increasing.

392
00:14:43,220 --> 00:14:46,680
A force law like this is,

393
00:14:46,680 --> 00:14:47,040
again,

394
00:14:47,040 --> 00:14:47,860
unphysical.

395
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:49,380
It never occurs in nature.

396
00:14:51,060 --> 00:14:54,040
The forces that occur in nature are called conservative.

397
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:57,460
And they are always of the following form.

398
00:14:57,740 --> 00:14:59,260
The components of a force,

399
00:14:59,260 --> 00:15:01,440
I'm speaking about a single particle now,

400
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:03,420
we'll generalize this to many particles,

401
00:15:03,620 --> 00:15:05,860
in fact we'll generalize it to arbitrary systems,

402
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:09,100
but let's take the case of a single particle.

403
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:11,580
The force,

404
00:15:11,580 --> 00:15:13,480
and now think of the force as a vector,

405
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:16,780
I'm drawing it in two dimensions,

406
00:15:16,780 --> 00:15:18,480
it could be in any number of dimensions,

407
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:22,260
is equal to minus the derivative,

408
00:15:24,220 --> 00:15:25,820
I'll write a formula and

409
00:15:25,820 --> 00:15:27,420
then I'll explain what it means.

410
00:15:29,860 --> 00:15:30,800
This formula,

411
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:34,920
this triangle is simply a symbol for derivatives,

412
00:15:34,920 --> 00:15:36,360
partial derivatives.

413
00:15:37,340 --> 00:15:40,620
Imagine that the potential energy is a function of position,

414
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:43,380
and if the position were two-dimensional,

415
00:15:43,380 --> 00:15:44,300
as it is here,

416
00:15:44,980 --> 00:15:47,000
it would be a function of x and y.

417
00:15:48,520 --> 00:15:50,140
This is the potential energy,

418
00:15:50,140 --> 00:15:50,620
u.

419
00:15:52,540 --> 00:15:55,300
This formula really just means

420
00:15:55,300 --> 00:15:58,060
that each component of the force,

421
00:15:59,140 --> 00:16:00,780
the x component of the force,

422
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:03,320
and the y component of the force,

423
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:07,000
are equal to minus the derivative,

424
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,000
in this case with respect to x,

425
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:11,120
of u of x and y,

426
00:16:12,540 --> 00:16:14,680
and minus the derivative with respect to

427
00:16:14,680 --> 00:16:16,820
y of u of x and y.

428
00:16:18,820 --> 00:16:20,320
That's what this symbol means.

429
00:16:20,620 --> 00:16:22,420
It means the collection of derivatives,

430
00:16:22,420 --> 00:16:23,860
partial derivatives,

431
00:16:24,640 --> 00:16:26,700
with respect to the individual coordinates.

432
00:16:27,760 --> 00:16:29,100
So what it says then,

433
00:16:29,100 --> 00:16:31,820
is the components of force in a given direction

434
00:16:31,820 --> 00:16:34,750
are proportional to how fast the

435
00:16:34,750 --> 00:16:37,680
potential energy is changing along that direction.

436
00:16:38,860 --> 00:16:39,440
Okay.

437
00:16:40,640 --> 00:16:41,220
Alright,

438
00:16:41,220 --> 00:16:43,730
let's use this to prove the conservation

439
00:16:43,730 --> 00:16:46,240
of energy for the motion of a particle.

440
00:16:46,700 --> 00:16:48,160
I did it last time,

441
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:48,800
but I,

442
00:16:49,540 --> 00:16:50,440
as I said,

443
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:51,440
I was getting a little bit tired,

444
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:52,380
so I want to do it again,

445
00:16:52,480 --> 00:16:54,380
and just do it as review.

446
00:16:55,850 --> 00:16:56,140
Okay.

447
00:16:57,460 --> 00:17:01,760
Let's define the quantity of the total energy

448
00:17:01,760 --> 00:17:05,220
as the sum of kinetic energy plus potential energy.

449
00:17:05,560 --> 00:17:05,980
Okay,

450
00:17:05,980 --> 00:17:06,420
what about,

451
00:17:06,420 --> 00:17:07,339
what is kinetic energy?

452
00:17:07,619 --> 00:17:08,780
I'll define it for you now.

453
00:17:09,099 --> 00:17:10,240
By definition,

454
00:17:10,240 --> 00:17:12,839
for a particle moving,

455
00:17:12,839 --> 00:17:13,940
it's one half

456
00:17:13,940 --> 00:17:17,859
the mass of the particle times the velocity squared.

457
00:17:18,920 --> 00:17:20,660
The velocity squared means,

458
00:17:20,660 --> 00:17:23,319
if there's more than one component of velocity,

459
00:17:23,319 --> 00:17:25,299
it means the sums of the

460
00:17:25,299 --> 00:17:27,280
squares of the components of the velocity.

461
00:17:27,540 --> 00:17:28,260
So in this case,

462
00:17:28,260 --> 00:17:28,960
with two dimensions,

463
00:17:28,960 --> 00:17:30,140
it would mean one half

464
00:17:31,220 --> 00:17:34,240
m vx squared plus vy squared.

465
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:38,440
More generally,

466
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:40,320
I could write it as one

467
00:17:40,320 --> 00:17:42,200
half the mass of the object

468
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:46,340
times the sum over the components of vi squared.

469
00:17:48,180 --> 00:17:48,740
Sum,

470
00:17:48,740 --> 00:17:52,040
meaning vx squared plus vy squared plus vz squared,

471
00:17:52,040 --> 00:17:55,800
or whatever the number of directions of space is.

472
00:17:56,960 --> 00:17:57,560
Okay,

473
00:17:57,560 --> 00:17:58,620
that's the kinetic energy.

474
00:17:58,860 --> 00:18:00,720
So that's usually called T.

475
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:03,200
Again,

476
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:05,460
just like P stands for momentum,

477
00:18:05,460 --> 00:18:07,420
T stands for kinetic energy.

478
00:18:07,560 --> 00:18:08,340
Don't ask me why.

479
00:18:09,740 --> 00:18:10,580
And then,

480
00:18:10,580 --> 00:18:13,000
the other contribution to the energy...

481
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:16,200
Is that also why U is potential?

482
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:17,100
Yeah,

483
00:18:17,100 --> 00:18:18,140
it's also why U is potential.

484
00:18:18,800 --> 00:18:20,760
A lot of people use V for potential.

485
00:18:22,300 --> 00:18:24,520
But that gets mixed up with voltage,

486
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:28,680
which is potential energy divided by charge.

487
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:32,340
So I use U and I steer clear of V,

488
00:18:32,540 --> 00:18:33,740
but other people use V.

489
00:18:33,880 --> 00:18:35,680
It also gets confused with velocity.

490
00:18:36,700 --> 00:18:38,360
T plus U.

491
00:18:39,560 --> 00:18:41,500
That is the total energy.

492
00:18:43,760 --> 00:18:46,030
I want to prove that it's

493
00:18:46,030 --> 00:18:48,300
conserved as a consequence of Newton's equation,

494
00:18:48,660 --> 00:18:49,720
F equals m a.

495
00:18:50,540 --> 00:18:52,020
What does it mean that it's conserved?

496
00:18:52,040 --> 00:18:55,360
It means that its time derivative is zero.

497
00:18:55,740 --> 00:18:57,830
So all we have to

498
00:18:57,830 --> 00:18:59,920
do is take its time derivative,

499
00:19:00,979 --> 00:19:02,640
use Newton's equations,

500
00:19:03,060 --> 00:19:04,970
and prove that everything cancels out

501
00:19:04,970 --> 00:19:06,880
when we take the time derivative.

502
00:19:07,180 --> 00:19:07,940
That's the exercise.

503
00:19:08,240 --> 00:19:09,080
And it's not very hard.

504
00:19:09,180 --> 00:19:09,700
Let's do it.

505
00:19:11,560 --> 00:19:12,200
Okay,

506
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:14,160
so let's calculate the time

507
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:16,120
derivative of the kinetic energy.

508
00:19:17,340 --> 00:19:20,200
Derivative with respect to time of kinetic energy.

509
00:19:20,560 --> 00:19:21,720
That is...

510
00:19:21,720 --> 00:19:22,620
Here it is right here.

511
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:23,900
Here's the kinetic energy.

512
00:19:24,020 --> 00:19:25,040
One half mv squared.

513
00:19:25,860 --> 00:19:27,360
m is not changing.

514
00:19:28,020 --> 00:19:29,240
Mass is fixed.

515
00:19:29,700 --> 00:19:31,380
One half is not changing.

516
00:19:31,660 --> 00:19:34,260
The thing which might change is the velocity.

517
00:19:35,940 --> 00:19:36,500
This,

518
00:19:36,500 --> 00:19:37,220
of course,

519
00:19:37,220 --> 00:19:38,900
is the sum of squares of velocities.

520
00:19:39,480 --> 00:19:40,320
So it's a sum.

521
00:19:46,300 --> 00:19:50,840
mv sub i times dv sub i by dt.

522
00:19:50,840 --> 00:19:52,880
Now what I've done is I've

523
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:54,920
said that the derivative of a square,

524
00:19:55,820 --> 00:19:58,120
namely the derivative of v squared,

525
00:19:58,460 --> 00:20:01,020
is v times the derivative of v.

526
00:20:01,360 --> 00:20:03,890
The derivative of a square of something

527
00:20:03,890 --> 00:20:06,420
is the something times its own derivative.

528
00:20:08,740 --> 00:20:09,340
Whoops.

529
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:11,080
I forgot a factor of...

